===

Usage Guide

--

A. Lora Weight

  • 0.1 ~ 0.4 -- is to combine multiple faces or features, or if you experience overbaking

  • 0.5 ~ 0.7 -- is a balanced weight to get still accurate feature but with more flexiblity

  • 0.8 ~ 1.0 -- is to create accurate representation of the features.

B. CFG Scale

  • Lower CFG Scale means AI gets more creative and less overbaking problems.

  • Higher CFG Scale means results get very accurate with training sets and more prone to overbaking problems.

  • Dynamic CFG Threshold, using this method allows you to bump up quality and achieve photorealistic easily, but with lycoris i found out recently that this method actually lower success rate, so only use when you are composing with a Lora / model that works fine with this method.

C. Sampling Steps, High Res Fix & Upscaling

  • I like to use sampling steps at 50, with high res step at 20, or 1/2 of sampling steps.

  • I find that 2M Karras works better and faster than SDE Karras. with ERSGAN 4x+ method + ERSGAN 4x for Upscaling. This method actually gives quite good result without being too sharp or too plasticky

  • Upscaling - GPFGAN @0.25, Codeformer @0.3 & Codeformer Weight @0.15 seems to yield superior results to me.

--

Combining with Attribute LoRa / LyCoris

You may need to do your own testing, but using character at weight -0.2 below attribute lora weight yields superior results, if for some reason one features persists not showing or overbake, you may want to lower the weight of the overbaked feature Lora, and then use emphasis () to boost the specific attribute you want.

DDetailer / ADetailer Script

If subject face is small / far away use: DDetailer Script with bbox anime face with default settings except denoiser at 0.2-0.3. You can combine this LoRa with a lot of other Style / Attire / Pose / Acts LoRa, Also works well with character LyCoris.

How to install this script? I kinda forget how because its a bit complicated beacuse you need to install stuff from venv. but a quick google search will land you somewhere in tutorial page.

Enjoy.

Marin Kitagawa LoHA & LoRAs (Marin, Kuroe Shizuku, Black Lobelia, Prisoner Veronica, and Liz Kyun) - Sono Bisque Doll (Character)

файл на civitaiстраница на civitai

This is a series of LOHA and LORAs of the character Marin Kitagawa from the anime and manga Sono Bisque Doll. It is trained on several outfits and all of her cosplay appearances in the anime.

Marin's LoHA contains several trained outfits, including her school uniform, her bikini, her off shoulder dress, her blue and green flannel shirt, her hoodie, and her kimono. To prompt Marin in her normal uniform, enter "<lora:MarinKitagawa:strength>Marin Kitagawa, school uniform, plaid skirt, black choker". Other outfit prompts include, "flower halterneck bikini, blue and yellow striped shirt, lace choker, string choker, off-shoulder shirt, high-waist skirt, gray jacket, track pants, gray hoodie, kimono". Each of these models can have the "anime screencap" style from the anime when prompted.

Marin's other cosplay outfit LORAs all have their own specific trigger words. Use each respective LORA and their trigger words to prompt them.

For Kuroe Shizuku, enter "Kuroe Shizuku, rose bonnet, black collar, gothic dress, thighhighs".

For Black Lobelia, enter "Black Lobelia, heterochromia, military hat, military jacket, leotard dress, black gloves, black thighhigh boots, black gem".

For Prisoner Veronica, enter "Prisoner Veronica, white belt collar, white belt bra, white shorts, yellow eyes, sharp teeth"

For Liz Kyun, enter "Liz Kyun, frilled crop top, frilled panties, black socks". "wings, tail" are optional.

All of these models were trained on AnythingElsev4.5 at Clip Skip 2. They're very fun to customize, so have fun with them!

Fire Emblem Heroes Style

файл на civitaiстраница на civitai

I saw richyrich515 make a FEH Style LoRA and was inspired to make my own.

I only used about 300 images. This LoCON is great at replicating the style of named character in FEH. It's a bit outdated though. It doesn't even have FE16 characters, but that's not an issue and can be rectified easily in future versions.

Keep the weight around 0.8.

This LoCON mixes well with my other FE-Style LoCONs and generated portrait ratio images well.

This LoCON was trained without damage or attack images to keep the output a bit cleaner.

I trained at 600x768. I'll definitely train it larger for v2 in order to preserve more details and have more faithful outputs.

I recommend a prompt like this:

FEH, Fire Emblem, Laevatein (Fire Emblem), Laevatein (Fire Emblem: Heroes), simple background, 1girl, solo, weapon, dark-skinned female, dark skin, black and red armor, long hair, full body, red eyes, twintails, holding, feather trim, holding weapon, pink hair, hair ornament, sword, bangs, bare shoulders, breasts, gradient, multicolored hair, gradient hair, holding sword, looking at viewer, closed mouth, armor, standing, medium breasts, hand on hip, gauntlets, orange hair, thighhighs, sleeveless, cleavage, shiny, shiny hair, feathers

You can replace the italicized words for other named characters in FEH.
